ade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/3/03 7:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3247.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Planes weapon itemization.</span><hr size=1> Hello all,<br>
<br>
I was just looking through Alakazam (sp?) and parusing all the equipment that I'll never get <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> .  One thing that I noticed and stood out as blaringly out of whack was the difference in weapon ratios between the top Knight weapons and the top Warrior weapons.<br>
<br>
I play both a Paladin and a Warrior and like both classes equally well, and still can't understand this.  It would seem logical to me that Warrior weapons should have better ratio stats on them.  And to top it all off, arguably the best damaging two hander in the game is a Knight only weapon.<br>
<br>
Seems to me like warriors got a little shafted at the uber equipment level in PoP.  As I yet to have a character over level 40, I could be wrong here, but the two hander situation seems really screwed up.  If all the top tier mobs riposte as much as I've heard, then two handed weapons is the only real way to go to keep DPS up while still tanking.  And the fact that Knights seem better with two handers than Warriors do (gaining a 3rd attack AA), it just compounds the issue.<br>
<br>
Anyway, I just had to get that out of my system.  I guess you kinda just have to play the cards your dealt.  Not like it's going to make me quit playing EQ or either my Pally or Warrior.<br>
<br>
See you all online.<br>
<br>
 <p>Alucard Crimsonblade<br>
