<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.oboo.org">OBOO!</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alucardcrimsonblade>Alucard Crimsonblade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/4/03 10:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3247.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   RE:</span><hr size=1> I'm not disputing that Warriors do still do more DPS (about 8% or so on average) when similarly equipped, but I am talking when maxed out.<br>
<br>
I would like to see some kind of information on a Knight and a Warrior wearing the exact same equipment and a Vanazir, having all of their melee skills maxed out (pertinent ones at least).  I am sure the warrior would outdamage the Knight (based upon pure melee only).  However have the knight switch over to the Greatblade of Chaos and see how things stack up.  <br>
<br>
I am not saying the better ratio would necissarily make the Knight out damage the Warrior, but I sure bet the % difference would at least decrease.<br>
<br>
This is what I refer to when I say itemization.  Why is arguable the best damaging two hander in the game (ratio wise) a Knight only weapon, and the closest thing to it that a Knight can't wield is Aggression, which doesn't even compare.  I just think that either a Warrior only weapon on par with the Greatblade of Chaos is warranted or make the GBoC War/Pal/SK equipable.<br>
<br>
And like I said before, this is comming from someone who plays both a Paladin and a Warrior and likes both equally well.  I can honestly say that I am not biased one way or another.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=eldryc>Eldryc</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>is a Formidable Opponent</span><br>  Posts: 172<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/4/03 10:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3247.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   ..</span><hr size=1> yeah, i've never really understood why they have that class penalty of lower weapon skills on knights supposedly to balance them, but then they offset part of that balance by making the knight weapons have a better ratio.  When you do that, what's the point of the penalty?  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=elty>elty</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/6/03 10:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3247.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: ..</span><hr size=1> war do more damage mostly due to higher skill (thus ATK), not better weapon. and, SK can outdamage war if they want to try. <p>LV 65 Maestro <!--EZCODE LINK START--